Chrysocyon brachyurus Data Preparation

Author

Florencia Grattarola

Published

July 6, 2023

Data preparation for modelling for Chrysocyon brachyurus, with the covariates bio_10, bio_14, elev, and grass (selected in the previous step).

  • Basemaps
equalareaCRS <-  '+proj=laea +lon_0=-73.125 +lat_0=0 +datum=WGS84 +units=m +no_defs'
Latam_projected <- st_read('data/Latam_vector.shp', quiet = T)
Latam_countries <- sf::st_read('data/Latam_vector_countries.shp', quiet = T) %>% sf::st_transform(crs=equalareaCRS)
Latam <- st_union(st_make_valid(Latam_projected))
Latam.raster <- terra::rast('data/Latam_raster.tif')
Latam.raster.countries <- terra::rast('data/Latam_raster_countries.tif')

# IUCN range distribution
cbrachyurus_IUCN <- sf::st_read('big_data/cbrachyurus_IUCN.shp', quiet = T) %>% sf::st_transform(crs=equalareaCRS)

MAP.IUCN <- tm_graticules(alpha = 0.3) +
    tm_shape(Latam_countries) +
    tm_fill(col='grey90') +
    tm_borders(col='grey60', alpha = 0.4) +
    tm_shape(cbrachyurus_IUCN) +
    tm_fill(col='grey20', alpha = 0.4) +
    tm_layout(legend.outside = T, frame.lwd = 0.3, scale=1.2, legend.outside.size = 0.1)

Covariates

The following covariates were chosen using the âvariableSelectionâ script:

  • bio_10: Mean Temperature of Warmest Quarter
  • bio_14: Precipitation of Driest Month
  • elev: Elevation
  • grass: Grasslands
Code 
elev <- rast(here::here('big_data/elev_high.tif'))
bio <- rast(here::here('big_data/bio_high.tif'))
grass <- rast(here::here('big_data/grass_high.tif'))
grass <- resample(grass, bio, method='bilinear')

# resample and scaled values for PO
env_100k_unscaled <- terra::resample(env, Latam.raster, method='bilinear') %>% 
  classify(cbind(NaN, NA))

env_100k_resampled <- env_100k_unscaled %>% scale() # scaled values to 0 mean and sd of 1

Data for the model

Presence-only data

Code 
# calculate area in each raster cell
PO_cbrachyurus.area <- terra::cellSize(PO_cbrachyurus_time1_raster[[1]], unit='m', transform=F) %>% 
  classify(cbind(NaN, NA)) %>% terra::values()

# calculate coordinates for each raster cell
PO_cbrachyurus.coords <- terra::xyFromCell(PO_cbrachyurus_time1_raster, cell=1:ncell(PO_cbrachyurus_time1_raster)) %>% as.data.frame()
names(PO_cbrachyurus.coords) <- c('X', 'Y')

# number of cells in the rasters (both the same)
PO_cbrachyurus.cell <- 1:ncell(PO_cbrachyurus_time1_raster)

# with the environmental variables values for each cell
PO_cbrachyurus.env <- env_100k_resampled[] # scaled values

# with the mean accessibility value for each cell
PO_cbrachyurus.acce <- acce_100k_resampled # scaled values

# calculate point count in each raster cell
PO_cbrachyurus_time1.count <- PO_cbrachyurus_time1_raster %>%
    classify(cbind(NaN, NA)) %>% terra::values() %>% as_tibble %>% 
  dplyr::select(count)

PO_cbrachyurus_time2.count <- PO_cbrachyurus_time2_raster %>%
    classify(cbind(NaN, NA)) %>% terra::values() %>% as_tibble %>% 
  dplyr::select(count)

PO_cbrachyurus.countries <- Latam.raster.countries %>% classify(cbind(NaN, NA))

# save time1 and time2 datasets 
PO_cbrachyurus_time1.model.data <- data.frame(PO_cbrachyurus.coords,
                                            pixel = PO_cbrachyurus.cell[],
                                            area = PO_cbrachyurus.area,
                                            pt.count = PO_cbrachyurus_time1.count,
                                            env = PO_cbrachyurus.env,
                                            acce = PO_cbrachyurus.acce[], 
                                            country = PO_cbrachyurus.countries[])

PO_cbrachyurus_time2.model.data <- data.frame(PO_cbrachyurus.coords,
                                            pixel = PO_cbrachyurus.cell[],
                                            area = PO_cbrachyurus.area,
                                            pt.count = PO_cbrachyurus_time2.count,
                                            env = PO_cbrachyurus.env,
                                            acce = PO_cbrachyurus.acce[], 
                                            country = PO_cbrachyurus.countries[])

PA_cbrachyurus.pixel.time2 <- terra::cells(PO_cbrachyurus_time2_raster, vect(st_centroid(PA_cbrachyurus_time2_blobs))) 

# mode to calculate the most frequent value for the blob - this needs to be changed to getting the %are for each landcover
mode_raster  <- function(x, na.rm = FALSE) {
  if(na.rm){ x = x[!is.na(x)]}
  ux <- unique(x)
  return(ux[which.max(tabulate(match(x, ux)))])
}

PA_cbrachyurus.env.time1 <- terra::extract(x = env, y = vect(PA_cbrachyurus_time1_blobs), fun = mean, rm.na=T) %>% 
  mutate(across(where(is.numeric), ~ifelse(is.nan(.), NA, .))) %>% scale()

PA_cbrachyurus.env.time2 <- terra::extract(x = env, y = vect(PA_cbrachyurus_time2_blobs), fun = mean, rm.na=T) %>% 
  mutate(across(where(is.numeric), ~ifelse(is.nan(.), NA, .))) %>% scale()

Extra: Datasets in the covariate space

The range (and interquartile range) of values for each covariate that is sampled by each dataset

Code 
getRangeIQR <- function(env_PX){
  env_PX.df <- tibble(env= character(),
                          range = numeric(),
                     iqr = numeric(),
                     stringsAsFactors=FALSE)
  
  for (i in 1:ncol(env_PX)){
    df <- tibble(env = names(env_PX[i]),
             range = range(env_PX[[i]], na.rm=T)[2],
             iqr=  IQR(env_PA[[i]], na.rm = T))
    env_PX.df <- rbind(env_PX.df, df)
  }
  return(env_PX.df)
}
